metadata.title: Cessna 172
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna produced 1 prototype of the Cessna 172 in 1973.
Reims produced 55 FR172K aircraft between 1978 and 1981.
The FR172K was known as the Reims Rocket.
The FR172K Reims Rocket was produced for the 1977 through 1981 model years.
Cessna introduced a retractable landing gear version of the Cessna 172 in 1980.
Cessna designated the retractable landing gear version as the 172RG.
Cessna marketed the 172RG as the Cutlass RG.

text:
1 (1973 prototype), 725 (1977), 205 (1978), 270 (1979), 200 (1980), and 55 (1981) built, plus 85 (30 in 1977, 55 in 197881) by Reims as the FR172K Reims Rocket for the 1977 through 1981 model years.

172RG Cutlass RG

Cessna introduced a retractable landing gear version of the 172 in 1980, designating it as the 172RG and marketing it as the Cutlass RG.
